OL,7,FShe said she believed this decision
OL,8,Fwas in breach of her employer's equal
OL,9,Fopportunities policy and disciplinary
OL,10,Fcode of conduct and that it failed to
OL,11,Fprovide her with a safe and secure
OL,12,Fworking environment.
OL,14,FThe store is in Northern Ireland, but
OL,15,Ffor legal reasons, cannot be named.
OL,17,FMs Storey told UTV that she bottled up
OL,18,Fwhat happened until one day, she broke
OL,19,Fdown and confided in her dad, who was
OL,20,Fproud of her for speaking out.
